columns.name: vendorid
columns.description: A designation for the technology vendor that provided the record. CMT=Creative Mobile Technologies VTS= VeriFone, Inc. DDS=Digital Dispatch Systems

columns.name: tpep_pickup_datetime
columns.description: The date and time when the meter was engaged.

columns.name: dropoff_datetime
columns.description: The date and time when the meter was disengaged.

columns.name: passenger_count
columns.description: The number of passengers in the vehicle. This is a driver-entered value.

columns.name: trip_distance
columns.description: The elapsed trip distance in miles reported by the taximeter.

columns.name: pickup_longitude
columns.description: Longitude where the meter was engaged.

columns.name: pickup_latitude
columns.description: Latitude where the meter was engaged.

columns.name: ratecodeid
columns.description: The final rate code in effect at the end of the trip. 1= Standard rate 2=JFK 3=Newark 4=Nassau or Westchester 5=Negotiated fare 6=Group ride

columns.name: store_and_fwd_flag
columns.description: This flag indicates whether the trip record was held in vehicle memory before sending to the vendor, aka “store and forward,” because the vehicle did not have a connection to the server. Y= store and forward trip N= not a store and forward trip

columns.name: dropoff_longitude
columns.description: Longitude where the meter was disengaged.

columns.name: dropoff_latitude
columns.description: Latitude where the meter was disengaged.

columns.name: fare_amount
columns.description: The time-and-distance fare calculated by the meter.

columns.name: extra
columns.description: Miscellaneous extras and surcharges. Currently, this only includes the $0.50 and $1 rush hour and overnight charges.

columns.name: mta_tax
columns.description: $0.50 MTA tax that is automatically triggered based on the metered rate in use.

columns.name: tip_amount
columns.description: Tip amount – This field is automatically populated for credit card tips. Cash tips are not included.

columns.name: tolls_amount
columns.description: Total amount of all tolls paid in trip.

columns.name: total_amount
columns.description: The total amount charged to passengers. Does not include cash tips.

view.description:
Filter cards by selecting date ranges on date/time cards, typing freeform text into search cards, or clicking the columns in the column card.

This dataset includes trip records from all trips completed in yellow taxis in NYC in 2010. Records include fields capturing pick-up and drop-off dates/times, pick-up and drop-off locations, trip distances, itemized fares, rate types, payment types, and driver-reported passenger counts. The data used in the attached datasets were collected and provided to the NYC Taxi and Limousine Commission (TLC) by technology providers authorized under the Taxicab Passenger Enhancement Program (TPEP). The trip data was not created by the TLC, and TLC makes no representations as to the accuracy of these data.
